trans-unit.source: Storage Analytics Metrics aggregates transaction data and capacity data for a storage account.
trans-unit.target: Storage Analytics Metrics aggregates transaction data and capacity data for a storage account.

trans-unit.source: Transactions metrics are recorded for the Blob, Table, and Queue services.
trans-unit.target: Transactions metrics are recorded for the Blob, Table, and Queue services.

trans-unit.source: Currently, capacity metrics are only recorded for the Blob service.
trans-unit.target: Currently, capacity metrics are only recorded for the Blob service.

trans-unit.source: Transaction data and capacity data is stored in well-known tables, as described in the following table:
trans-unit.target: Transaction data and capacity data is stored in well-known tables, as described in the following table:

trans-unit.source: While these names are still supported, it’s recommended that you switch to using the tables listed below.
trans-unit.target: While these names are still supported, it’s recommended that you switch to using the tables listed below.

trans-unit.source: Read-access geo-redundant replication must be enabled.
trans-unit.target: Read-access geo-redundant replication must be enabled.

trans-unit.source: Read-access geo-redundant replication must be enabled.
trans-unit.target: Read-access geo-redundant replication must be enabled.

trans-unit.target: For more information about Metrics, see <link xlink:href="c944c107-684c-47bf-92bf-5ce32689b7ae" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metrics in Storage Analytics</link>.

trans-unit.source: Two entities are stored in the <legacyItalic>$MetricsCapacityBlob</legacyItalic> table each day, one summarizing storage account blob and container size details and the other summarizing size details of the <codeInline>$logs</codeInline> container.
trans-unit.target: Two entities are stored in the <legacyItalic>$MetricsCapacityBlob</legacyItalic> table each day, one summarizing storage account blob and container size details and the other summarizing size details of the <codeInline>$logs</codeInline> container.

trans-unit.source: A timestamp in UTC that represents the starting hour for metrics, in the following format: <codeInline>YYYYMMddThhmm</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: A timestamp in UTC that represents the starting hour for metrics, in the following format: <codeInline>YYYYMMddThhmm</codeInline>.

trans-unit.source: Because data is only reported once per day, <codeInline>hhmm</codeInline> (hour and minutes) will always be <codeInline>0000</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: Because data is only reported once per day, <codeInline>hhmm</codeInline> (hour and minutes) will always be <codeInline>0000</codeInline>.

trans-unit.source: This value is the <legacyItalic>PartitionKey</legacyItalic> for all entries in the table.
trans-unit.target: This value is the <legacyItalic>PartitionKey</legacyItalic> for all entries in the table.

trans-unit.source: Indicates whether the capacity table entity applies to user data or Storage Analytics data, in the following format: <codeInline>%%amp;lt;data|analytics%%amp;gt;</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: Indicates whether the capacity table entity applies to user data or Storage Analytics data, in the following format: <codeInline>%%amp;lt;data|analytics%%amp;gt;</codeInline>.

trans-unit.source: If the value is <codeInline>data</codeInline>, this table entity indicates capacity metrics for user data only.
trans-unit.target: If the value is <codeInline>data</codeInline>, this table entity indicates capacity metrics for user data only.

trans-unit.source: If the value is <codeInline>analytics</codeInline>, this table entity indicates capacity metrics for Storage Analytics data only, specifically the capacity consumed by the <codeInline>$logs</codeInline> blob container.
trans-unit.target: If the value is <codeInline>analytics</codeInline>, this table entity indicates capacity metrics for Storage Analytics data only, specifically the capacity consumed by the <codeInline>$logs</codeInline> blob container.

trans-unit.source: The amount of storage used by the storage account’s Blob service, in bytes.
trans-unit.target: The amount of storage used by the storage account’s Blob service, in bytes.

trans-unit.source: The number of blob containers in the storage account’s Blob service.
trans-unit.target: The number of blob containers in the storage account’s Blob service.

trans-unit.source: The number of committed and uncommitted blobs in the storage account’s Blob service.
trans-unit.target: The number of committed and uncommitted blobs in the storage account’s Blob service.

trans-unit.source: Each table that stores transaction data, whether by hour or by minute, uses the same schema.
trans-unit.target: Each table that stores transaction data, whether by hour or by minute, uses the same schema.

trans-unit.source: Additionally, each table writes two kinds of summary data:
trans-unit.target: Additionally, each table writes two kinds of summary data:

trans-unit.source: Service-level summary data, which contains hourly aggregates for a storage service.
trans-unit.target: Service-level summary data, which contains hourly aggregates for a storage service.

trans-unit.source: API-level summary data, which contains hourly aggregates for a specific API.
trans-unit.target: API-level summary data, which contains hourly aggregates for a specific API.

trans-unit.source: Each entry in a table entity only applies to transactions that occurred during the hour (for hourly metrics) or minute (for minute metrics) specified by <system>Time</system> (<legacyItalic>PartitionKey</legacyItalic>).
trans-unit.target: Each entry in a table entity only applies to transactions that occurred during the hour (for hourly metrics) or minute (for minute metrics) specified by <system>Time</system> (<legacyItalic>PartitionKey</legacyItalic>).

trans-unit.source: For hour metrics, a timestamp in UTC that represents the starting hour for metrics, in the following format: <codeInline>YYYYMMddThhmm</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: For hour metrics, a timestamp in UTC that represents the starting hour for metrics, in the following format: <codeInline>YYYYMMddThhmm</codeInline>.

trans-unit.source: This value is the partition key for all entries in the table.
trans-unit.target: This value is the partition key for all entries in the table.

trans-unit.source: For minute metrics, the format is the same, but the minute value is an approximate indication of the time when the transactions were executed.
trans-unit.target: For minute metrics, the format is the same, but the minute value is an approximate indication of the time when the transactions were executed.

trans-unit.source: Transactions from earlier minutes may be aggregated into the transaction for the current minute if they were missed in the previous interval.
trans-unit.target: Transactions from earlier minutes may be aggregated into the transaction for the current minute if they were missed in the previous interval.

trans-unit.source: A combination of <system>AccessType</system> and <system>TransactionType</system>, in the following format: <codeInline>%%amp;lt;user|system%%amp;gt;;%%amp;lt;all|api-name%%amp;gt;</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: A combination of <system>AccessType</system> and <system>TransactionType</system>, in the following format: <codeInline>%%amp;lt;user|system%%amp;gt;;%%amp;lt;all|api-name%%amp;gt;</codeInline>.
